                                <li>
                                    <strong>    Can anyone colour their hair after a hair transplant? </strong>                                                            
                                    <p>Hair Transplant has proved to be a life-changing experience for so many people. But, it’s essential to carefully follow all the instructions of surgeons before and after the transplant. The healing process takes quite a time after the surgery. When your hair starts growing naturally, any grey hair in it can potentially dampen your newly established self-esteem. You can colour your hair after a hair transplant. But you need to remember one thing, your scalp is susceptible and fragile at this point. Applying harsh chemicals, bleaching agents, and peroxides might irritate your scalp and impair your newly implanted grafts. This can hamper your recovery process and the quality of transplanted hair. Therefore, we will advise you to wait for a period of four to six weeks before dying or colouring your hair. Your scalp gets enough time to heal considerably and allow the implants to fix firmly to your roots. </p>
                                    
                                    <p>The DHI Chennai surgeons recommend you wait for at least six weeks after your hair transplant surgery. You can easily color your hair after this period, as your scalp and grafts will get enough time to heal. Remember, results come from consistency. It’s important to note that the healing process varies from person to person. You need to be patient and wait to color your hair. Don’t try to do it by yourself. You can damage your implanted hair. Always get a professional to do this work as they have expertise on how to do it. They let you know which color will suit your hair better and dye your transplanted hair by following all the safety procedures. To get more in-depth information, reach out to the DHI Chennai clinic and seek assistance from our experts. We help you understand which options will work best for you.  </p>
                                    
